HEADWORD: Stowaway
<hw>Stow"a*way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who conceals
himself board of a vessel about to leave port, or on a railway train, in
order to obtain a free passage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

